SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1781330678
OL,3,CBritish artist David Hockney dies,
OL,4,Caged 88
OL,6,FIn particular, as an openly gay man at
OL,7,Fa time when homosexuality was still
OL,8,Fillegal in England, he
OL,9,Fenthusiastically embraced the
OL,10,Fopportunity to explore his sexuality.
OL,12,FHe produced a series of paintings
OL,13,Ffeaturing naked or semi-naked men
OL,14,Fwhich he later described as
OL,15,F"homosexual propaganda".
OL,17,F"I felt it should be done," he said.
OL,18,F"Nobody else would use it as a subject
OL,19,Fbecause it was a part of me. It was a
OL,20,Fsubject I could treat humorously."
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@WO]yD@AOUyD@[O]zD@AOU|D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
